This is an open source Android application. Please feel free to fork, bug fix
and commit back.

This is a simple book catalogue application, to store a list of your books.
Books can be added either manually, by ISBN, or by barcode.

Compared to BookCatalogue 5.2.2, this application brings:

Version 1.0.0:
* Modernisation to Android 6 (Marshmallow) bringing lots of new UI goodies.
* Generally more consistent in usage and layout.
* UI translations 99\% complete.
* Cover thumbnails and log files moved to dedicated sub folders.
* Configurable websites to search for data.
* New Search websites: isfdb.org, kb.nl, stripinfo.be
* Better Anthology support (Edit/View/cross-book) and morphed into “Table of Content” or “TOC”
* TOC auto populated (ISFDB site only!).
* List of all works of an author.
* Reformatting of titles configurable.
* Language field shows the translated name in the current locale.
* More Locale support in general (Formatting & Sorting)
* Books & Anthology/TOC titles now have a “first published” field.
* Book Formats standardization.
* Book Editions (1st, book-club, etc).
* Book paid price.
* Book date acquired.
* Book pages is now alphanumeric
* Currency support for prices.
* Styles exported/imported in XML format.
* Export of all tables can also be done in XML (no import yet).
* Full support for rotating the screen at any time.
* External site id usage for direct identification & links.
* Experimental: New Search website: OpenLibrary
* Removed: The old “Classic” view is gone.
* Bug fixes


